<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01, About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">A holding cabinet failing FDA 140°F at lunch service is a health-code conversation, not a maintenance call.</h2>

        <p>Heated holding cabinets maintain cooked food at safe holding temperatures (140°F minimum per FDA Food Code) between cooking and service. LA banquet kitchens, catering operations, hotel breakfast buffets, hospital food service, and institutional dining all depend on holding cabinets for hot food transport (catering off-site), long-shift food holding (banquet service), multi-station meal prep, and food safety compliance.</p>

        <div class="alto-callout">
          <p><strong>Alto-Shaam dominates 70%+ of the holding cabinet market.</strong> The Halo Heat technology (radiant gentle heat, no fan circulation) preserves food quality during 4 to 8 hour holds in a way fan-forced heat cabinets can't match. We service the full Alto-Shaam Halo Heat lineup: 1000-S, 750-S, 500-S full-size cabinets, plus 500-2D and 1200-TH/III mobile carts. Combitherm holding mode covered on the <a href="/brands/alto-shaam-oven-repair/">Alto-Shaam oven page</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <p>Other brands we cover: <strong>Cres Cor</strong> (independent Ohio, dominant in mobile holding carts for banquet wheel-style transport), <strong>Carter-Hoffmann</strong> (Standex Food Service, HL2 series heat and hold cabinets), <strong>Winston CVap</strong> (controlled vapor humidity-managed holding, premium for moisture-sensitive foods), and <strong>Metro</strong> (InterMetro / Ali Group, C5 series heated holding and food transport).</p>

        <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.  scope for adjacent commercial gas and refrigeration work. BBB Accredited. Phones answered 24/7. Mobile cabinet, stationary cabinet, FDA compliance verification, all on the same call.</p>
