<!-- TYPICAL FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Typical Failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What our techs see most often, in rough order of frequency</h2>
    <p class="lead">Eight failure modes account for nearly every holding cabinet call. Half are routine wear at predictable intervals. The other half cluster on mobile carts in heavy catering use.</p>

    <div class="failures-list">
      <div class="failure-row">
        <div class="num">1</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Halo Heat element burnout (Alto-Shaam, year 8–12)</h3>
          <p>Radiant heating element deterioration. Most Alto-Shaam cabinets carry two elements; one usually fails first and the cabinet still holds at reduced setpoint range, which is why the failure often gets caught only when food drops under 140°F. Replacement $480–$720 per element.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="failure-row">
        <div class="num">2</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Thermostat drift (year 5–8)</h3>
          <p>Temperature control accuracy degrades. The displayed 160°F holds at 130°F actual, which is a direct food safety compliance issue under FDA Food Code. Calibration $290–$440, replacement $440–$720. We test before condemning.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="failure-row">
        <div class="num">3</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Door gasket compression</h3>
          <p>Heat seal degrades from years of door slams and thermal cycling. Once it leaks, the cabinet pulls more energy and temperature drifts at the door side. Replacement $260–$420.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="failure-row">
        <div class="num">4</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Door hinge wear (mobile carts especially)</h3>
          <p>Catering carts get opened and closed dozens of times per event. Hinges loosen, doors sag, gaskets stop sealing. $180–$340 per hinge.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="failure-row">
        <div class="num">5</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Wheel and caster failure (Cres Cor mobile carts especially)</h3>
          <p>Heavy-duty caster wear from continuous transport across kitchen tile, parking-lot asphalt, banquet hall carpet. $80–$180 per caster. Easy fix, often deferred until two or three wheels are failing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="failure-row">
        <div class="num">6</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Humidity control failure (Winston CVap)</h3>
          <p>Water injection system specific to CVap. When it fails, the cabinet drops back to dry-heat behavior and the food quality advantage disappears. $440–$720 to repair the injection system.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="failure-row">
        <div class="num">7</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Power cord and plug damage (mobile carts)</h3>
          <p>Frequent plugging and unplugging at multiple venues stresses the connection. Cords get rolled over by other carts, plugs get yanked. $180–$340 to replace cord assembly with strain relief.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="failure-row">
        <div class="num">8</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Insulation degradation (older units year 12+)</h3>
          <p>Thermal efficiency loss, temperature drift, exterior runs warmer than spec. Re-insulation is a specialty fabric and insulation trade we don't perform; on units past year 12 with insulation failure, replacement is usually the right answer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CONFIGURATIONS -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03, Configurations We Service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Stationary cabinets, mobile carts, and Combitherm holding mode</h2>

    <div class="config-grid">
      <div class="config-card">
        <div class="tag">Most Common LA</div>
        <h3>Alto-Shaam Halo Heat Stationary</h3>
        <p>Full-size 1000-S (26 hotel pan), 3/4 size 750-S (18 pan), compact 500-S (12 pan). Halo Heat radiant technology preserves food quality during 4 to 8 hour holds.</p>
        <div class="skus">1000-S · 750-S · 500-S</div>
      </div>
      <div class="config-card">
        <div class="tag">Catering / Banquet</div>
        <h3>Alto-Shaam Halo Heat Mobile</h3>
        <p>Wheeled transport carts with Halo Heat radiant technology. Catering operations, hotel banquet transport, off-site events.</p>
        <div class="skus">500-2D · 1200-TH/III</div>
      </div>
      <div class="config-card">
        <div class="tag">Combi Cross-Reference</div>
        <h3>Alto-Shaam Combitherm Holding Mode</h3>
        <p>CT Express, CT Proformance combi ovens have integrated holding mode. Holding cabinets often paired with combi ovens in premium kitchens. See <a href="/commercial/oven-repair/combi-oven-repair/" style="color:#ff8080;">combi oven repair</a>.</p>
        <div class="skus">CT Express · CT Proformance</div>
      </div>
      <div class="config-card">
        <div class="tag">Mobile Cart Specialty</div>
